<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/15126168-anu-vuokko">Anu Vuokko</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s not very eloquently written as the author isn&apos;t a professional writer. But I think it would be weird if the author used long, eloquent sentence s<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's not very eloquently written as the author isn't a professional writer. But I think it would be weird if the author used long, eloquent sentence structures since it is written from the view of an ex-homeless, recovering drug-addict. It's all about the story.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
